Subject: [PATCH 195/800] ARM: dts: am33xx: Mark ocmcram node with map-exec

Mark the ocmcram node with map-exec dt flag so that the generic sram
driver knows to map our sram as executable as the PM code will execute
from there.

Signed-off-by: Dave Gerlach <d-gerlach@ti.com>
[zou: Original patch taken from PROCESSOR-SDK-LINUX-AM335X 02_00_01_07]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/am33xx.dtsi |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/am33xx.dtsi b/arch/arm/boot/dts/am33xx.dtsi
index cc8bce9..65c2a5d 100644
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/am33xx.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/am33xx.dtsi
@@ -784,6 +784,7 @@
 		ocmcram: ocmcram@40300000 {
 			compatible = "mmio-sram";
 			reg = <0x40300000 0x10000>; /* 64k */
+			map-exec;
 		};
 
 		elm: elm@48080000 {
